                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.002/18.]</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 73.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Sir: I have the honor to inform the Department that the newly appointed Cabinet
                    of Dr. Francisco Andrade Marin, President of the Chamber of Deputies, in charge
                    of the Executive Power, is as follows: Minister of Foreign Relations, Señor
                    Antonio Arcos; Minister of War, General Juan Francisco Navarro; Minister of
                    Hacienda, J. F. Intriago; Minister of the Interior, Dr. José Maria Ayora;
                    Minister of Public Instruction, Dr. Léon B. Becerra.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rutherfurd Bingham</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
